.PP
Demote ourselves from the role of domain controller\&.
.SS "domain exportkeytab keytab [options]"
.PP
Dumps Kerberos keys of the domain into a keytab\&.
.SS "domain functionalprep [options]"
.PP
Prepare a domain for functional level upgrade\&. If
\fB\-\-functional\-level\fR
is not used, the latest supported version is used (currently 2016)\&.
.PP
There are two aspects to this preparation, relating to the forest and the domain\&. By default both are run\&. If either of
\fB\-\-forest\-prep\fR
or
\fB\-\-domain\-prep\fR
are used, only the corresponding preparation is made\&. If both arguments are used together, all preparation is done, just as when neither is used\&.
.PP
\-H, \-\-URL
.RS 4
LDB URL for database or target server\&.
.RE
.PP
\-\-functional\-level [2008_R2|2012|2012_R2|2016]
.RS 4
The functional level to prepare for\&. The default is 2016\&.
.RE
.PP
\-\-forest\-prep
.RS 4
Run forest preparation only (unless \-\-domain\-prep is also used)\&.
.RE
.PP
\-\-domain\-prep
.RS 4
Run domain preparation only (unless \-\-forest\-prep is also used)\&.
.RE
.SS "domain info ip_address [options]"
.PP
Print basic info about a domain and the specified DC\&.
.SS "domain join dnsdomain [DC|RODC|MEMBER|SUBDOMAIN] [options]"
.PP
Join a domain as either member or backup domain controller\&.
.SS "domain kds root-key"
.PP
Manage Key Distribution Service root keys\&.
.SS "domain kds root-key create [options]"
.PP
Create KDS root keys
.PP
\-H, \-\-URL
.RS 4
LDB URL for database or target server\&.
.RE
.PP
\-\-use\-start\-time=["now"|iso8601 or LDIF time string]
.RS 4
The key will be valid from this time\&.
.sp
Valid time format are the string "now", the LDIF format
\fBYYYYmmddHHMMSS\&.0Z\fR, or the ISO format
\fBYYYY\-mm\-dd[*HH[:MM[:SS[\&.fff[fff]]]][+HH:MM[:SS[\&.ffffff]]]]\fR
where the \*(Aq*\*(Aq can be any character, and the optional last \*(Aq[+HH:MM[:SS[\&.ffffff]]]\*(Aq is a timezone offset (e\&.g\&. \*(Aq+00:00\*(Aq for UTC)\&.
.RE
.PP
\-\-json
.RS 4
Output results in JSON format\&.
.RE
.SS "domain kds root-key delete --name={GUID}"
.PP
Delete the named KDS root key\&. Use
\fBsamba\-tool domain kds root\-key list\fR
to find the name of the key\&.
.PP
\-H, \-\-URL
.RS 4
LDB URL for database or target server\&.
.RE
.PP
\-\-name=NAME
.RS 4
The name of the key to delete\&. It will be a GUID\&.
.RE
.PP
\-v, \-\-verbose
.RS 4
Print all attributes (except secret ones, unless \-\-show secrets is used)\&.
.RE
.PP
\-\-json
.RS 4
Output results in JSON format\&.
.RE
.SS "domain kds root-key list [options]"
.PP
List KDS root keys\&. The newest keys are listed first\&.
.PP
\-H, \-\-URL
.RS 4
LDB URL for database or target server\&.
.RE
.PP
\-\-show\-secrets
.RS 4
Print secret or potentially sensitive attributes, namely msKds\-RootKeyData and msKds\-SecretAgreementParam\&.
.RE
.PP
\-v, \-\-verbose
.RS 4
Print more attributes (but not secret ones, unless \-\-show secrets is also used)\&.
.RE
.PP
\-\-json
.RS 4
Output results in JSON format\&.
.RE
