.SS "user addunixattrs username uid-number [options]"
.PP
Add RFC2307 attributes to a user\&.
.PP
This command adds Unix attributes to a user account in the Active Directory domain\&.
.PP
The username specified on the command is the sAMaccountName\&.
.PP
You must supply a unique uid\&.
.PP
Unix (RFC2307) attributes will be added to the user account\&.
.PP
If you supply a group id with \*(Aq\-\-gid\-number\*(Aq, this will be used for the users Unix \*(AqgidNumber\*(Aq attribute\&.
.PP
If \*(Aq\-\-gid\-number\*(Aq is not supplied, the users Unix gidNumber will be set to the one found in \*(AqDomain Users\*(Aq, this means Domain Users must have a gidNumber attribute\&.
.PP
If \*(Aq\-\-unix\-home\*(Aq is not supplied, the users Unix home directory will be set to /home/DOMAIN/username\&.
.PP
If \*(Aq\-\-login\-shell\*(Aq is not supplied, the users Unix login shell will be set to \*(Aq/bin/sh\*(Aq
.PP
If \-\-\-gecos\*(Aq is not supplied, the users Unix gecos field will be set to the user\*(Aqs \*(AqCN\*(Aq attribute\&.
.PP
Add \*(Aqidmap_ldb:use rfc2307 = Yes\*(Aq to the smb\&.conf on DCs to use these attributes for UID/GID mapping\&.
.PP
The command may be run from the root userid or another authorised userid\&. The \-H or \-\-URL= option can be used to execute the command against a remote server\&.
.PP
Example1:
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
samba\-tool user addunixattrs User1 10001
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.sp
Example1 shows how to add RFC2307 attributes to a domain enabled user account, Domain Users will be set as the users gidNumber\&.
.PP
The users Unix ID will be set to \*(Aq10001\*(Aq, provided this ID isn\*(Aqt already in use\&.
.PP
Example2:
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
samba\-tool user addunixattrs User2 10002 \-\-gid\-number=10001 \-\-unix\-home=/home/User2
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.PP
Example2 shows how to add RFC2307 attributes to a domain enabled user account\&.
.PP
The users Unix ID will be set to \*(Aq10002\*(Aq, provided this ID isn\*(Aqt already in use\&.
.PP
The users gidNumber attribute will be set to \*(Aq10001\*(Aq
.PP
The users Unix home directory will be set to \*(Aq/home/user2\*(Aq
.PP
Example3:
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
samba\-tool user addunixattrs User3 10003 \-\-gid\-number=10001 \-\-login\-shell=/bin/false \-\-gecos=\*(AqUser3 test\*(Aq
.fi
.if n \{\
.RE
.\}
.PP
Example3 shows how to add RFC2307 attributes to a domain enabled user account\&.
.PP
The users Unix ID will be set to \*(Aq10003\*(Aq, provided this ID isn\*(Aqt already in use\&. The users gidNumber attribute will be set to \*(Aq10001\*(Aq\&. The users Unix login shell will be set to \*(Aq/bin/false\*(Aq\&. The users gecos field will be set to \*(AqUser3 test\*(Aq\&.
.PP
\-H URL, \-\-URL=URL
.RS 4
LDB URL for database or target server
.RE
.PP
\-\-gid\-number=GROUP_ID
.RS 4
User\*(Aqs Unix/RFC2307 GID
.RE
.PP
\-\-unix\-home=DIR
.RS 4
User\*(Aqs Unix/RFC2307 home directory
